cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of single-image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method that reduces the number of computations required, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its method using various benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
